-- 
Sudan Cotton Co. Reports Increase in Revenue for 2010/2011

-- B y   S a l m a   E l   W a r d a n y
-- 
2011-09-16T15:07:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-16/sudan-cotton-co-reports-increase-in-revenue-for-2010-2011.html
Sudan Cotton Co. said revenue
increased to 6.8 billion Sudanese pounds ($2.5 billion) in
2010/2011 from 4.35 billion pounds a year earlier, Al Raaie Al-
Aam newspaper reported, citing data given by the company.  Sudan Cotton plans to increase its area under cultivation
to 1.2 million feddans (1.25 million acres) of cotton over the
next three years, from 90,000 feddans in 2010, the Khartoum-
based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Salma El Wardany in Khartoum at 
 selwardany@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Paul Richardson  at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net . 